        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 1 at 3:04PM MDT by NWS Great Falls MT</headline>
        <description>At 304 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 19
miles southwest of Dillon, moving northeast at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Dillon, Clark Canyon, and Beaverhead Rock State Park.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
